               AWMInfoTitleIndustrial site information:Delaware City Refining Company, LLC (AKA, Valero Refinery at Delaware City, Premcor and Motiva)





                 AWMInfoBodyThe  Delaware City Refinery, most recently owned and operated by PBF, was previously known as The Premcor Refining Group, Inc., Valero Refinery at Delaware City, and  Motiva). The facility refines crude oil into automobile gasoline, home heating oil, and a variety of other petroleum products. Delaware City Refinery Company, LLC purchased the facility on June 1, 2010 from Valero. Previously, Premcor purchased the facility from Motiva Enterprises, L.L.C. on May 1, 2004, and in 2005 became a subsidiary of Valero Energy Corporation. The Valero Energy Corp. based in San Antonio, Tex., was incorporated in Delaware.   



Secretary's Order 202013-A-0022 Mechanical Integrity Program Evaluation

Fluid Coker Unit Operating Permit 

Crude Upgrade and Optimization AKA "Bin 1" Project

Motiva Supplemental Environmental Project Semiannual Report November 2008

Frozen Earth Storage Conciliation Order
For more information on this facility, please visit DNREC’s Environmental Navigator database and the Toxics Release Inventory.
















